news.title: Mumbai NCLT allows 90-day extension of insolvency resolution for Lavasa Corp
news.para: The planned city project is undergoing a fresh CIRP after the NCLT, in September 2024, directed that the entire process be restarted, following the successful bidder's failure to implement the approved resolution plan within the specified time frame.

news.title: Study to map gaps in mass transit system plan as new Gurugram metro corridor taking shape
news.para: HMRTC has floated a tender for a study, which will be undertaken by a consultant agency expected to be onboarded shortly, with completion targeted within four months.

news.title: Lucknow development body to convert 4,000 rented properties into freehold
news.para: The committee includes assistant engineer KP Gupta, Pankaj Sonkar from the rent department and Manoj Kumar Bharti, surveyor from the acquisition department.

news.title: DDA moves Delhi HC, says RERA cannot issue it directions
news.para: Questioning the real estate regulator's competence to order DDA to register the housing projects, the latter stated that it was not a real estate promoter like private builders, but an independent authority whose activities were covered under the DDA Act and related Nazul rules.

news.title: Gurugram: Vatika G21's builder demolishes boundary wall, residents seek administration’s intervention
news.para: According to RWA, the incident occurred around 2am on Sunday night when the staffers of the developer allegedly switched off the area lights and demolished the five-foot-high wall.

news.title: Have issued norms to monitor use of loan money by builders: RBI to SC
news.para: Under the subvention scheme, banks disburse the sanctioned amount directly to the the builders, who then have to pay EMIs on the sanctioned loan amount, until possession of the flats is handed over to homebuyers.

news.title: E-Khata mandatory for building plan approval from July 1: Bengaluru civic body
news.para: According to BBMP, from July 1, the procedure of forwarding property ownership records to the Revenue Department for verification will also be discontinued.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh CM distributes land ownership rights to 25 people in Kinnaur
news.para: The certificates were distributed under the Forest Rights Act, 2006, which have been pending for many years. Sukhvinder Singh Sukhu said that under the Act, land leases have already been allotted to 460 individuals across the state.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat, Birla Corp incentive demand at risk after West Bengal scraps subsidy schemes
news.para: An official of Dalmia Cement (Bharat) Ltd (DCBL), a wholly owned subsidiary of Dalmia Bharat, stated that it was supposed to receive Rs 236.32 crore along with 8 per cent interest under the now-revoked 'WB State Support for Industries Scheme 2013'.

news.title: Ayodhya land prices soar as circle rates hiked by up to 200 per cent
news.para: The new rates, which came into effect on Monday, have particularly impacted areas within a 10-kilometre radius of the Ram Janmabhoomi Temple, where rates have jumped by over 150 per cent.

news.title: International Finance Corporation invests ₹420 crore in Birla Estates' two projects
news.para: IFC will invest about ₹148 crore in company's Manjri project in Pune having approximately 3.13 million sq ft saleable area and about ₹272 crore in its Thane project with approximately 6.43 million sq ft saleable area.

news.title: Shaula Real Estates buys apartment in Naman Xana for ₹226 crore in Mumbai
news.para: The apartment was purchased from Naman Residency and Karp Estate. The duplex unit has a carpet area of 856 sq meters (9,214 sq ft). The total built-up area of the apartment is 1,067 sq meters (11,485 sq ft).

news.title: Hyderabad civic body plans tribunal to tackle issue of unauthorised constructions
news.para: The move assumes significance in view of the nearly 2.5 lakh writ petitions pertaining to illegal constructions filed in the high court in the past five years.

news.title: Oswal Pumps files DRHP for Rs 890 crore IPO
news.para: The IPO comprises a fresh issue aggregating up to Rs 890 crore and an OFS of up to 81 lakh equity shares by Vivek Gupta, the promoter selling shareholder.

news.title: Consolidation in cement to continue, expects 7-8% industry growth in FY26: Dalmia Bharat
news.para: Dalmia Cement expects a bounce back in growth to 7-8 per cent for the cement sector in FY26, which witnessed a subdued cement demand growth of around 5 per cent last year amidst the general elections and erratic rains, according to the latest annual report of India's fourth-largest cement manufacturer.

news.title: Illegal sand smuggling busted in multiple operations in Nagpur district
news.para: The Bhiwapur police launched the first operation on June 7 after receiving a tip-off about illegal sand movement near Hotel Wada in mouja Taas.

news.title: Karnataka: Over 800 property documents registered on June 1
news.para: The initiative, aimed at easing weekday congestion at sub-registrar offices, brought in more than Rs 3 crore in revenue through stamp duty and registration fees on that one day alone.

news.title: Birla Opus Paints files abuse complaint with CCI against Asian Paints
news.para: Grasim Industries, which owns Birla Opus Paints, reportedly filed the complaint in November 2024, alleging that Asian Paints threatened dealers with reduced credit limits and withdrawal of contracts if they engaged with Grasim.

news.title: Bank of Baroda, HDFC Bank reduce lending rate by up to 50 bps, 10 bps
news.para: HDFC Bank reduced its Marginal Cost of Funds-based Lending Rates (MCLR) by 10 basis points across tenure, which will benefit borrowers whose loans are linked to this benchmark.

news.title: Mohali development body to slash enhancement charges by ₹800 per sq metre
news.para: Gmada had taken an undertaking from all allottees at the time of plot allotment, agreeing to pay the enhancement charges as and when decided by the authority.
